    <text id="R122440T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate General P. G. T. Beauregard reports to Jefferson Davis in July, 1861,
                    from his lines along Bull Run Creek. He asks Davis to notify Johnston via
                    Staunton of his movements.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    No. 64. Reports of Gen. G.T. Beauragard, commanding Confederate Army of the
                    Potomac, of operations from July 17 to 20.
                    <name type="recipient">JEFFERSON DAVIS,<lb/> President of the Confederate
                        States:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-07-17">July 17, 1861.</date>
                        <name type="place">MANASSAS,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>The enemy has assailed my outposts in heavy force. I have fallen back on the line
                    of Bull Run, and will make a stand at Mitchell's Ford.</p>
                <p>If his force is overwhelming I shall retire to the Rappahannock Railroad Bridge,
                    saving my command for defense there and future operations. Please inform
                    Johnston of this, via Staunton, and also Holmes. Send forward any
                    re-enforcements at the earliest possible instant and by every possible means.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>G.T. BEAUREGARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
